so I can't stay for long.

248
00:13:44,889 --> 00:13:46,682
Did your AC go over the rules?

249
00:13:47,266 --> 00:13:49,143
No, but, uh, she seemed busy.

250
00:13:49,226 --> 00:13:50,811
All right. Well, look, the big thing

251
00:13:50,893 --> 00:13:53,188
is there's no switching eternities
after you've chosen.

252
00:13:53,271 --> 00:13:55,439
No visiting other eternities, no nothing.

253
00:13:55,982 --> 00:13:57,649
Eternity is eternity.

254
00:13:57,732 --> 00:13:58,942
It's forever.

255
00:13:59,025 --> 00:14:02,779
What if I didn't go along with the rules?
What are they gonna do, kill me again?

256
00:14:02,862 --> 00:14:04,655
Technically they can't kill you again.

257
00:14:04,738 --> 00:14:05,740
But you break a rule,

258
00:14:05,823 --> 00:14:09,159
you overstay your welcome,
or you try switching eternities,

259
00:14:09,951 --> 00:14:11,414
they'll put you into the void.

260
00:14:11,995 --> 00:14:13,205
Is that like hell?

261
00:14:13,288 --> 00:14:14,455
As close as there is.

262
00:14:15,497 --> 00:14:18,333
It's just blackness, for eternity.

263
00:14:20,544 --> 00:14:21,544
Um…

264
00:14:23,421 --> 00:14:26,465
My wife has cancer. It's terminal.

265
00:14:27,966 --> 00:14:29,009
I'm sorry to hear that.

266
00:14:29,092 --> 00:14:32,652
Worst part about death is the guilt
you feel for the ones you left behind.

267
00:14:34,013 --> 00:14:36,682
I know, and I told her that I was
always gonna take care of her.

268
00:14:36,765 --> 00:14:39,851
And now she's sick,
and dealing with all this.

269
00:14:39,934 --> 00:14:42,062
Um… Could I get a mixer with that?

270
00:14:42,145 --> 00:14:43,608
That is absolutely disgusting.

271
00:14:47,524 --> 00:14:49,193
Morning, sleepyhead.

272
00:14:49,276 --> 00:14:50,652
Morning, sweetie.

273
00:14:55,448 --> 00:14:56,865
What the hell?

274
00:14:57,657 --> 00:14:59,159
What's going on? How did you get in here?

275
00:14:59,242 --> 00:15:01,388
-Larry, you don't remember?
-Remember what?

276
00:15:02,453 --> 00:15:04,246
No, we didn't. Did we?

277
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:06,457
Nah, I'm just joking. I have a key.

278
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:08,250
-Why do you have a key?
-It's not important.

279
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:11,085
So, you seemed to have
a good time last night.

280
00:15:11,586 --> 00:15:14,172
I'm dead. You wouldn't think hangovers
would be a thing.

281
00:15:14,254 --> 00:15:16,632
I know, right?
It's a common misconception.

282
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:19,677
I got a question.

283
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,261
Mm-hmm. Hit me with it.

284
00:15:24,013 --> 00:15:27,641
So, everyone working here, they don't want
to go to their eternity. Why?

285
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:30,602
Some people haven't accepted death,

286
00:15:31,269 --> 00:15:34,188
and some people are waiting
for their loved ones.

287
00:15:34,271 --> 00:15:35,273
Oh.

288
00:15:35,356 --> 00:15:39,484
And others haven't decided yet,
and those are the worst ones.

289
00:15:40,902 --> 00:15:42,154
Well, why did you stay?

290
00:15:42,237 --> 00:15:45,489
That is a story
for another time.

291
00:15:45,572 --> 00:15:47,449
-Mmm.
-So, tell me.

292
00:15:48,242 --> 00:15:50,076
Where you going? Did you decide?

293
00:15:52,954 --> 00:15:55,790
No. I… I need to see where Joan is.

294
00:15:55,872 --> 00:15:58,417
-Mmm.
-How can I tell how close she is?

295
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,211
No, I'm sorry. It doesn't work like that.
I can't do that.

296
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:04,338
So all that looking down from above stuff,
that's just a bunch of BS?

297
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:06,048
Mmm. You're annoyed?

298
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,675
-No, I'm not annoyed.
-You look annoyed.

299
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:09,885
What about everybody who died before me?
Where's my parents?

300
00:16:09,968 --> 00:16:11,136
How do I see them?

301
00:16:11,219 --> 00:16:14,930
- You could definitely go see your parents.
- But then, you know, you'd be…

302
00:16:15,013 --> 00:16:17,391
-Be with my parents for eternity.
-Eternity.

303
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,352
That's why we usually recommend
for you to do you.

304
00:16:22,311 --> 00:16:24,898
And just know that everyone
is existing pretty damn good.

305
00:16:24,981 --> 00:16:26,147
You know what I mean?

306
00:16:30,277 --> 00:16:32,737
You know, Joan always thought of death

307
00:16:32,820 --> 00:16:35,531
as one more surprise
waiting around the corner.

308
00:16:35,614 --> 00:16:37,366
-Mmm.
-And she loved surprises.

309
00:16:37,449 --> 00:16:38,992
But she was a librarian though, right?

310
00:16:39,075 --> 00:16:40,744
Yeah, they can like surprises too.

311
00:16:40,827 --> 00:16:41,828
Oh.

312
00:16:43,329 --> 00:16:45,289
So if I wanted to wait,
what do I have to do?

313
00:16:45,372 --> 00:16:46,874
Get a job? Be a bartender?

314
00:16:46,957 --> 00:16:49,876
No. You wish.
It's cleaning work.

315
00:16:49,959 --> 00:16:52,169
-Do you know how to do laundry?
-Yeah.

316
00:16:54,505 --> 00:16:55,772
At least the room is nice.

317
00:16:56,673 --> 00:16:59,718
Yeah. But it's for clients.

318
00:16:59,801 --> 00:17:02,678
So if you don't decide,
then you have to go…

319
00:17:02,761 --> 00:17:04,096
Well, I was told there is no hell.

320
00:17:04,179 --> 00:17:06,599
-The basement.
-Oh.

321
00:17:06,682 --> 00:17:08,725
The rooms are more functional
in the basement.

322
00:17:08,808 --> 00:17:11,019
-Mmm.
-Jesus, you went straight to hell.

323
00:17:13,104 --> 00:17:15,147
You look like you hate people.
Try Hermit World.

324
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:17,357
Hi. Excuse me…

325
00:17:18,358 --> 00:17:20,443
Do you want a little sniffle? And you?

326
00:17:27,615 --> 00:17:31,452
Final call for Cowboy World 167.

327
00:17:37,707 --> 00:17:38,708
Smoke, sir?

328
00:17:42,253 --> 00:17:43,545
It could be tomorrow.

329
00:17:43,628 --> 00:17:46,882
Or she could hang on for another,
what, six or seven months?

330
00:17:46,965 --> 00:17:49,467
I mean, I guess I could
set everything up for her.

331
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:52,595
And I could, you know, make sure
it's… it's how she likes it,

332
00:17:52,678 --> 00:17:54,430
really make it feel like a home.

333
00:17:55,013 --> 00:17:56,848
Larry, that is so romantic.

334
00:17:58,558 --> 00:18:01,018
- I guess it is a little romantic.
- It's so romantic.

335
00:18:01,101 --> 00:18:03,562
- I can be romantic.
- I…

336
00:18:03,645 --> 00:18:06,231
-'Cause I know how she likes things.
-You do.

337
00:18:53,687 --> 00:18:54,688
Oh.

338
00:18:54,771 --> 00:18:57,774
I really think you picked a good one.
You are not going to regret this, Larry.

339
00:18:57,857 --> 00:19:00,783
-Hey, hey, uh, would you do me a favor?
-Yeah, sure can do.

340
00:19:01,402 --> 00:19:02,737
Could you give Joan this letter for me?

341
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:04,613
No can do. That's against the rules.

342
00:19:04,696 --> 00:19:06,614
Plus, why do you need a letter
when you got me?

343
00:19:06,697 --> 00:19:10,327
Beach Land 239,
now boarding at gate 12.

344
00:19:10,410 --> 00:19:12,078
It was a pleasure working with you.

345
00:19:12,161 --> 00:19:13,161
Yeah.

346
00:19:17,582 --> 00:19:18,582
Bye.

347
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:21,168
Bye.

348
00:19:23,712 --> 00:19:25,422
Sorry. Oh.

349
00:19:26,631 --> 00:19:27,632
Ow.

350
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:31,468
Shoot.

351
00:19:31,969 --> 00:19:32,970
Okay.

352
00:19:41,144 --> 00:19:45,105
Mind your step.
Disorientation is normal.

353
00:19:52,194 --> 00:19:53,363
Joan.

354
00:19:53,446 --> 00:19:54,654
Joan!

355
00:19:55,405 --> 00:19:56,823
Joan! Joan!

356
00:19:56,906 --> 00:19:59,034
That's my wife.

357
00:19:59,117 --> 00:20:00,677
Yeah. Come on, buddy.

358
00:20:01,618 --> 00:20:03,618
-It's that way.
-Yeah, okay. Yeah, yeah.

359
00:20:05,539 --> 00:20:08,075
Come on, come on, come on, come on!
Come on.

360
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:10,502
There you go.

361
00:20:10,585 --> 00:20:15,297
The newly dead from
North America, arriving in Junction 301.

362
00:20:17,632 --> 00:20:20,635
Oh, excuse me. Excuse me.
Sorry, where am I?

363
00:20:20,718 --> 00:20:22,845
Um, your AC will explain everything.

364
00:20:22,928 --> 00:20:25,555
- Okay. Okay.
- You know, it's just…

365
00:20:25,638 --> 00:20:28,558
Honey, your AC will explain everything.

366
00:20:33,729 --> 00:20:34,938
That looks nice.

367
00:20:35,439 --> 00:20:38,066
Joan. Joan! Joan.

368
00:20:38,149 --> 00:20:39,442
- Larry!
- Joan.

369
00:20:39,525 --> 00:20:42,694
-Sweetie. Ah, sweetie.
-Oh, my God.

370
00:20:42,777 --> 00:20:43,904
I missed you so much.

371
00:20:43,987 --> 00:20:47,657
-Hi. Oh. Oh, my God.
-Wow, look at you. Wow. I love this.

372
00:20:47,740 --> 00:20:51,744
I was, uh, I was in bed, and then I…
I thought I just came from a…

373
00:20:51,827 --> 00:20:53,162
-Baby, you look amazing.
-…a-a train.

374
00:20:53,245 --> 00:20:55,414
-Oh! Every time!
-Ow! Ow!

375
00:20:55,497 --> 00:20:59,209
God, every damn time, Larry.
I told you to slow down on the pretzels.

376
00:20:59,292 --> 00:21:01,252
-But, you… No, no, you never listen.
-I know, I know.

377
00:21:01,335 --> 00:21:02,628
Oh, you stop smiling.

378
00:21:02,711 --> 00:21:03,712
-Jo?
-Yeah.

379
00:21:03,795 --> 00:21:05,588
Listen to me, honey. I have shocking news.

380
00:21:05,671 --> 00:21:06,891
-You're dead.
-I'm dead.

381
00:21:07,256 --> 00:21:08,550
Yeah. How'd you know?

382
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:09,634
I mean…

383
00:21:09,717 --> 00:21:12,094
It took him forever to figure that out.

384
00:21:12,177 --> 00:21:13,804
-Not forever.
-Yeah, forever.

385
00:21:13,887 --> 00:21:16,974
-No.
-So you are the famous Joan.

386
00:21:17,057 --> 00:21:19,934
Okay, Larry. Way to marry up.

387
00:21:20,017 --> 00:21:22,937
-Yeah.
-So, uh, what-what now?

388
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:24,020
Yeah, so now, so...

389
00:21:24,103 --> 00:21:25,313
Was it cancer?

390
00:21:26,439 --> 00:21:28,358
That took you away from the world?

391
00:21:29,067 --> 00:21:30,234
So, who are you?

392
00:21:30,317 --> 00:21:33,487
Okay, honey. So listen,
now we finally get to have that holiday.

393
00:21:33,570 --> 00:21:35,905
And basically we can go
anywhere we want, but then that's it.

394
00:21:35,988 --> 00:21:38,491
It's like a one and done thing here.
They're very strict on that.

395
00:21:38,574 --> 00:21:40,452
Um, and if you want to go
to the mountains we can,

396
00:21:40,535 --> 00:21:43,829
because the snow and the cold's not
gonna kill you now, 'cause you're dead.

397
00:21:43,912 --> 00:21:45,747
-Back away from my client.
-I'm not near your client.

398
00:21:45,830 --> 00:21:46,999
-Back away.
-Shut up.

399
00:21:47,081 --> 00:21:49,208
I've been waiting for this golden goose
for 67 goddamn years.

400
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:50,293
-Oh, Lar?
-Hi.

401
00:21:50,376 --> 00:21:52,545
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- I'm so sorry about her.

402
00:21:52,628 --> 00:21:53,628
Who's that?

403
00:21:53,711 --> 00:21:56,006
I'm Ryan.
I'm your afterlife coordinator.

404
00:21:56,089 --> 00:21:57,090
Yeah.

405
00:21:57,173 --> 00:21:59,258
I know this can be
very, very overwhelming.

406
00:21:59,341 --> 00:22:01,260
It's a lot to absorb,
so I highly recommend just…

407
00:22:01,343 --> 00:22:05,680
…taking a deep breath in,
and… …out.

408
00:22:05,763 --> 00:22:07,723
Just breathe out.

409
00:22:41,668 --> 00:22:43,170
Oh. Hey. What's going on, guy?

410
00:22:43,253 --> 00:22:44,922
This was my, uh, bartender.

411
00:22:45,005 --> 00:22:48,132
I, um, guess I forgot to pay the tab.
I didn't realize there would be a tab.

412
00:22:48,215 --> 00:22:49,466
Nobody gave me any money.

413
00:22:50,509 --> 00:22:53,303
No way.

414
00:22:53,386 --> 00:22:55,222
Sorry. I forgot to ask your name.
What's your name again?

415
00:22:55,305 --> 00:22:56,723
I'm Luke.

416
00:22:56,806 --> 00:22:58,367
This is Luke. He's my bartender.

417
00:22:59,641 --> 00:23:00,976
Joan.

418
00:23:01,643 --> 00:23:02,853
Oh, no.

419
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:07,064
I never dreamt you this clearly.

420
00:23:08,482 --> 00:23:10,442
You're exactly how I dreamt you.

421
00:23:10,525 --> 00:23:12,569
Oof. Hard luck, Larry.

422
00:23:14,237 --> 00:23:16,281
No. Luke had a mustache.

423
00:23:16,363 --> 00:23:17,990
Yeah, well, Joanie hated it.

424
00:23:18,073 --> 00:23:20,952
So I shave it off every morning
hoping she's gonna show up.

425
00:23:21,035 --> 00:23:23,911
- Oh, my God.
- How romantic.

426
00:23:26,789 --> 00:23:27,832
And you did.

427
00:23:29,583 --> 00:23:30,656
Okay, sweetie.

428
00:23:32,252 --> 00:23:33,254
-Okay.
-Oh.

429
00:23:33,337 --> 00:23:34,754
-What you doing?
-Larry?

430
00:23:34,837 --> 00:23:36,256
-Okay, sweetie.
-I…

431
00:23:36,339 --> 00:23:37,465
- Let's go.
- Oh.

432
00:23:37,548 --> 00:23:39,050
-Who's this guy?
-The second husband.

433
00:23:39,133 --> 00:23:41,802
-I prefer current husband.
-The current husband.

434
00:23:41,885 --> 00:23:44,846
- Oh.
- Joanie, you're all right?

435
00:23:45,513 --> 00:23:46,514
Oh, my God.

436
00:23:46,597 --> 00:23:49,225
Honey. It was a lot for me too.

437
00:23:49,308 --> 00:23:53,019
Okay. I have to insist that I explain
exactly what's going on to my client.

438
00:23:53,102 --> 00:23:58,732
She clearly has
a very "difficult" decision to make.

439
00:23:58,815 --> 00:24:01,318
- Okay. Oh, that…
- Come on.

440
00:24:01,401 --> 00:24:04,717
- Oh, my God, he's really here.
- And very attractive.

441
00:24:05,446 --> 00:24:06,447
Is he taller?

442
00:24:06,530 --> 00:24:08,532
So when you said you were waiting…

443
00:24:09,116 --> 00:24:11,618
I conjured her image every day in my mind.

444
00:24:12,577 --> 00:24:17,331
Thought I did a good job,
but she's more stunning than I remember.

445
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,501
Okay. That's a line, Luke.

446
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:22,835
You were my bartender.

447
00:24:25,171 --> 00:24:26,172
Hmm?

448
00:24:26,255 --> 00:24:29,675
Nope. Nope. Nope.

449
00:24:31,093 --> 00:24:32,995
-Uh, mmm no.
-God, he looked so young.

450
00:24:33,761 --> 00:24:35,221
This will have to do.

451
00:24:35,304 --> 00:24:37,264
Was he always that young?

452
00:24:37,807 --> 00:24:39,142
That's a lot to take in.

453
00:24:39,225 --> 00:24:42,603
The love of your life waiting 67 years.

454
00:24:42,686 --> 00:24:43,979
And Larry.

455
00:24:44,062 --> 00:24:45,646
Larry is my husband.

456
00:24:45,729 --> 00:24:47,648
-One of two.
-Yeah.

457
00:24:47,731 --> 00:24:48,733
Oh, that's pretty.

458
00:24:48,816 --> 00:24:52,068
You'll feel much better after you change
out of that morbid ensemble.

459
00:24:52,151 --> 00:24:55,280
Ah. Oh. Oh.

460
00:24:55,363 --> 00:24:56,740
Yeah, that's pretty.

461
00:24:56,823 --> 00:24:58,782
That's… Oh, he's so young.

462
00:24:59,658 --> 00:25:01,785
Oh, he's so young. Oh, I don't…

463
00:25:01,868 --> 00:25:03,329
What's your ETA, doll?

464
00:25:03,412 --> 00:25:06,205
- Oh.
- How's it looking?

465
00:25:08,249 --> 00:25:09,875
So… What…

466
00:25:09,958 --> 00:25:11,584
What am I supposed to do, huh?

467
00:25:12,085 --> 00:25:14,755
I need you to tell me…
…what to do.

468
00:25:14,838 --> 00:25:17,381
Oh, my dear. Okay. I read your file.

469
00:25:17,965 --> 00:25:20,718
And you are smart,
passionate and decisive.

470
00:25:20,801 --> 00:25:22,260
Oh. I am?

471
00:25:22,927 --> 00:25:26,473
I have complete faith that you
will choose the right eternity…

472
00:25:26,556 --> 00:25:29,558
-Yeah.
-…and the right person to spend it with.

473
00:25:29,641 --> 00:25:31,185
-Mmm.
-You'll do.

474
00:25:31,268 --> 00:25:33,602
Do for what?

475
00:25:34,812 --> 00:25:36,230
Were you expecting someone, or…

476
00:25:36,313 --> 00:25:37,606
Were you?

477
00:25:38,524 --> 00:25:40,942
Uh…

478
00:25:41,025 --> 00:25:44,487
Oh, my God, Luke.
What a surprise.

479
00:25:45,154 --> 00:25:46,614
What the hell, Reese?

480
00:25:46,697 --> 00:25:49,575
It's Ryan,
and it's been Ryan for the last half hour.

481
00:25:49,658 --> 00:25:52,369
- Yeah.
- You look amazing.

482
00:25:52,452 --> 00:25:54,496
Yeah. I'm married.

483
00:25:54,579 --> 00:25:56,373
-To him.
-To Larry.

484
00:25:56,456 --> 00:25:58,290
And Larry seems nice.

485
00:25:58,373 --> 00:26:02,503
Look, Joan, you must have thought,
or hoped, that this might happen?

486
00:26:02,586 --> 00:26:06,881
Well, I mean, yeah. Yeah, yeah.
You know, I-I have imagined it.

487
00:26:06,964 --> 00:26:08,382
Great.

488
00:26:09,090 --> 00:26:10,425
Hi.

489
00:26:10,508 --> 00:26:12,594
- I'll leave you kids to it.
- Oh.

490
00:26:12,677 --> 00:26:13,762
Hi.

491
00:26:15,971 --> 00:26:17,890
Did you even read my file?

492
00:26:17,973 --> 00:26:20,476
You're more than words on a page
to me, buddy. You didn't even bring it up.

493
00:26:20,559 --> 00:26:22,602
Yeah, well, I had a lot on my mind.
I just died.

494
00:26:22,685 --> 00:26:26,648
So, I'm sorry that I forgot to mention
that my wife's ex might be hanging around.

495
00:26:26,731 --> 00:26:28,482
Technically,
