1490
01:20:06,198 --> 01:20:10,618
'Cause Joan and I, we'd just had
this conversation about starting a family.

1491
01:20:14,204 --> 01:20:16,373
Everything was laid out in front of us.

1492
01:20:18,208 --> 01:20:20,460
That was my happiest.

1493
01:20:25,172 --> 01:20:26,298
I'm 35.

1494
01:20:27,757 --> 01:20:33,053
Joan was pregnant with our second
and we went out to dinner one night.

1495
01:20:34,597 --> 01:20:37,182
The doctor was telling us
about all these new studies

1496
01:20:37,265 --> 01:20:39,948
where you're not supposed to drink
when you're pregnant.

1497
01:20:40,101 --> 01:20:43,979
And I got my glass of wine
and Joan took a sip of it,

1498
01:20:45,814 --> 01:20:48,609
and she just had this
little smile on her face.

1499
01:20:49,734 --> 01:20:56,531
And I don't know but, in that moment,
it just felt like we were a team.

1500
01:21:08,833 --> 01:21:09,835
You okay?

1501
01:21:09,918 --> 01:21:12,378
Oh, my God. I have to go.

1502
01:21:21,761 --> 01:21:23,054
What's going on?

1503
01:21:23,137 --> 01:21:24,430
Your AC will explain everything.

1504
01:21:24,513 --> 01:21:26,097
What's an AC?

1505
01:21:39,359 --> 01:21:42,903
We can go to this café on the Seine
where a fake Sartre

1506
01:21:42,986 --> 01:21:47,783
and fake Camus have a fight
and they have great pain au chocolat.

1507
01:21:48,282 --> 01:21:50,827
Was Camus the one
who always talked about death?

1508
01:21:50,910 --> 01:21:53,246
'Cause that just kinda
sounds pointless now.

1509
01:21:53,329 --> 01:21:54,580
Really?

1510
01:21:54,663 --> 01:21:57,541
You know, I read Sartre For Beginners.

1511
01:21:58,583 --> 01:22:00,293
How do you say Sartre?

1512
01:22:00,376 --> 01:22:02,170
-Sar… Sartre.
-Sartre.

1513
01:22:02,253 --> 01:22:03,462
And...

1514
01:22:03,963 --> 01:22:05,173
What's Larry doing here?

1515
01:22:05,256 --> 01:22:06,256
I…

1516
01:22:16,932 --> 01:22:20,310
-Please. Larry. I made up my mind, okay?
-Yeah.

1517
01:22:20,393 --> 01:22:23,396
-You know this is best. Okay?
-Your hair is different.

1518
01:22:24,938 --> 01:22:27,399
- Okay. Thank you.
- No.

1519
01:22:27,482 --> 01:22:30,485
Y-You never had it like that
when we were together.

1520
01:22:30,568 --> 01:22:32,611
No. I-I cut it after…

1521
01:22:35,197 --> 01:22:36,614
It suits you.

1522
01:22:37,865 --> 01:22:38,866
Larry.

1523
01:22:40,410 --> 01:22:41,661
You should go with Luke.

1524
01:22:42,828 --> 01:22:46,123
Okay? You deserve a shot
at that kind of love, honey.

1525
01:22:46,623 --> 01:22:50,042
That fiery, sparky kind.

1526
01:22:52,253 --> 01:22:54,796
But I was
so, so happy with you.

1527
01:22:56,298 --> 01:22:58,300
I… I know.

1528
01:22:58,383 --> 01:22:59,967
But you were happiest with him.

1529
01:23:00,884 --> 01:23:04,931
- It's okay.
- B-But what… What about you?

1530
01:23:06,973 --> 01:23:09,517
D-Don't worry about me.
I'll be in the sun.

1531
01:23:10,935 --> 01:23:13,062
Knowing you're happy makes me happy.

1532
01:23:14,980 --> 01:23:17,316
But it doesn't work unless you're happy.

1533
01:23:19,942 --> 01:23:21,193
Oh, Larry.

1534
01:23:33,037 --> 01:23:34,038
Okay.

1535
01:23:34,121 --> 01:23:37,123
You better go break the news
to Karen.

1536
01:23:37,957 --> 01:23:39,042
Okay.

1537
01:23:40,793 --> 01:23:41,793
Okay.

1538
01:23:44,880 --> 01:23:46,840
-Okay.
-It's the right thing.

1539
01:23:47,340 --> 01:23:48,799
Wow.

1540
01:25:13,787 --> 01:25:17,415
The train doors
will close in 30 minutes.

1541
01:25:17,998 --> 01:25:20,460
Babe, we shouldn't flaunt
our sexy love in front of his face.

1542
01:25:20,543 --> 01:25:22,003
He has no one.

1543
01:25:22,086 --> 01:25:23,295
-Hey.
-Hi.

1544
01:25:24,462 --> 01:25:25,922
How are you holding up, Lar?

1545
01:25:26,005 --> 01:25:27,966
Eh, I'm all right.

1546
01:25:28,049 --> 01:25:29,967
No hard feelings, right, Larry?

1547
01:25:30,050 --> 01:25:32,803
For what it's worth, I totally thought
you had it there for a moment.

1548
01:25:32,886 --> 01:25:34,054
Thanks.

1549
01:25:35,430 --> 01:25:37,557
What's this? Are you two together now?

1550
01:25:37,640 --> 01:25:40,893
- Yeah.
- We're gonna give it another go.

1551
01:25:40,976 --> 01:25:42,019
Good.

1552
01:25:42,102 --> 01:25:45,022
You really showed us that living
without someone is a hollow mess.

1553
01:25:45,105 --> 01:25:46,981
-What?
-I'm sorry.

1554
01:25:47,064 --> 01:25:48,608
- Okay.
- Give us a minute, please.

1555
01:25:48,691 --> 01:25:51,277
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Totally.
I miss you already.

1556
01:25:51,360 --> 01:25:53,319
God.

1557
01:25:55,780 --> 01:25:56,781
You wanna?

1558
01:26:06,247 --> 01:26:09,625
I gotta say,
I'm really proud of you, Larry.

1559
01:26:10,292 --> 01:26:12,043
You're doing the right thing.

1560
01:26:13,253 --> 01:26:14,546
I feel terrible.

1561
01:26:15,464 --> 01:26:17,423
Yeah. That happens.

1562
01:26:18,048 --> 01:26:20,551
Sometimes doing the right thing
does feel terrible.

1563
01:26:23,762 --> 01:26:26,250
So, you never told me why
you ended up staying here.

1564
01:26:29,016 --> 01:26:30,476
Um, coming here…

1565
01:26:33,353 --> 01:26:36,647
I'll just say that coming here
was an improvement for me.

1566
01:26:37,899 --> 01:26:41,902
Here, I get to help lost souls
find their happiness.

1567
01:26:43,111 --> 01:26:45,489
And that gives me a sense of purpose.

1568
01:26:45,572 --> 01:26:49,325
But after time, you stop caring
about what's best for people.

1569
01:26:49,825 --> 01:26:51,536
You're just pushing them along

1570
01:26:51,619 --> 01:26:55,497
and making sure the afterlife
is ticking over, you know?

1571
01:26:55,580 --> 01:26:56,706
Sell, sell, sell.

1572
01:26:59,416 --> 01:27:01,627
But then you came along.

1573
01:27:03,378 --> 01:27:05,630
Yeah. With that great ordinary love.

1574
01:27:07,340 --> 01:27:10,133
And you reminded me
of why I chose this place.

1575
01:27:11,051 --> 01:27:13,094
So, thank you for that, Larry.

1576
01:27:15,971 --> 01:27:18,349
Well, I guess you're welcome.

1577
01:27:23,937 --> 01:27:25,313
So…

1578
01:27:28,774 --> 01:27:30,651
Have you chosen your eternity?

1579
01:27:34,070 --> 01:27:36,364
Yeah, I think I have.

1580
01:27:48,666 --> 01:27:50,209
-Okay. Come on.
-What?

1581
01:27:50,292 --> 01:27:52,085
-Come on. Come on.
-Oh, God. Oh, no.

1582
01:27:52,168 --> 01:27:54,170
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

1583
01:27:55,380 --> 01:27:56,381
Oh, boy.

1584
01:27:57,422 --> 01:27:58,674
-Oh.
-Hey.

1585
01:27:59,383 --> 01:28:01,093
-Yeah.
-It's not bad, huh?

1586
01:28:01,176 --> 01:28:02,219
Oh, it's…

1587
01:28:05,137 --> 01:28:06,138
It's very charming.

1588
01:28:09,891 --> 01:28:11,768
Shit.

1589
01:28:12,811 --> 01:28:13,854
-A car crash.
-Oh.

1590
01:28:13,937 --> 01:28:15,938
Uh, old age. Cancer.

1591
01:28:16,647 --> 01:28:18,983
-War.
-Oh. War. Which one?

1592
01:28:19,066 --> 01:28:21,735
-I or II?
-Um, Korea.

1593
01:28:21,818 --> 01:28:23,319
-Which counts. Yeah.
-Oh.

1594
01:28:31,910 --> 01:28:33,119
Well done.

1595
01:28:33,202 --> 01:28:34,203
Thank you.

1596
01:28:40,417 --> 01:28:42,502
I love you so much.

1597
01:28:43,837 --> 01:28:44,837
So much.

1598
01:29:24,370 --> 01:29:26,248
- Hey.
- Hi.

1599
01:29:26,331 --> 01:29:29,499
Uh, so you like books?

1600
01:29:31,627 --> 01:29:33,336
Uh, yeah. I'm a librarian, so…

1601
01:29:33,419 --> 01:29:34,671
Can I help you with something?

1602
01:29:34,754 --> 01:29:36,130
Yeah. I can read.

1603
01:29:36,213 --> 01:29:38,174
That's good.
You're in the right place.

1604
01:29:38,257 --> 01:29:41,384
-What's that one?
-That's Dickens, Great Expectations.

1605
01:29:42,010 --> 01:29:43,178
Any good?

1606
01:29:44,054 --> 01:29:46,097
Um, you know, I haven't read it.

1607
01:29:46,180 --> 01:29:48,432
But that's
'cause I don't really love Dickens.

1608
01:29:48,515 --> 01:29:49,809
-Oh.
-It's a big controversy.

1609
01:29:49,892 --> 01:29:52,685
Yeah. I hate him.

1610
01:29:54,228 --> 01:29:55,814
You got a… You got a nice laugh.

1611
01:29:55,897 --> 01:29:57,439
Oh, thank you.

1612
01:30:00,192 --> 01:30:01,694
-I'm Joan.
-Larry.

1613
01:30:01,777 --> 01:30:03,528
-Nice to meet you, Larry.
-Nice to meet you.

1614
01:30:03,611 --> 01:30:05,613
Okay.

1615
01:30:06,697 --> 01:30:09,449
Okay.

1616
01:30:09,532 --> 01:30:11,409
-That's it, slow and steady.
-Okay.

1617
01:30:12,869 --> 01:30:14,203
Okay.

1618
01:30:14,286 --> 01:30:15,872
Keep up the good work, Joan.

1619
01:30:15,955 --> 01:30:18,165
Oh, yeah. Thanks, Simon.
Go fuck yourself.

1620
01:30:20,042 --> 01:30:21,668
- It's good.
- Yeah, really good.

1621
01:30:21,751 --> 01:30:23,169
-Oh, it feels good.
-Come on, let's go.

1622
01:30:23,252 --> 01:30:24,253
Okay.

1623
01:30:33,469 --> 01:30:34,553
What is that?

1624
01:30:35,972 --> 01:30:37,098
Who's that?

1625
01:30:38,932 --> 01:30:41,518
How is it that he already
needs to poop again?

1626
01:30:41,601 --> 01:30:43,437
Four months old
and he's already shitting like a man.

1627
01:30:43,520 --> 01:30:44,687
-Yeah.
-That's my boy.

1628
01:30:45,354 --> 01:30:47,148
- Oh, honey.
- What's that?

1629
01:30:47,231 --> 01:30:48,232
You stink.

1630
01:30:52,902 --> 01:30:55,155
Janet, Connor. Connor, Janet.

1631
01:30:55,238 --> 01:30:57,865
-They died doing a… What...
-Gender reveal party.

1632
01:30:57,948 --> 01:30:59,909
-Yeah. Gender reveal party.
-Yeah. There was so much blood.

1633
01:30:59,992 --> 01:31:01,327
Everywhere. Just oozing.

1634
01:31:01,410 --> 01:31:03,161
We didn't see it coming.
We'd al… We looked in.

1635
01:31:03,244 --> 01:31:04,662
We were like,
"Oh, what's going on in here?"

1636
01:31:04,745 --> 01:31:06,080
Boom! Blew our heads right off.

1637
01:31:06,163 --> 01:31:07,918
-I love it when you do that.
-Whoa.

1638
01:31:14,044 --> 01:31:15,587
Thank you, Fenwick.

1639
01:31:23,928 --> 01:31:26,513
Are you sure you don't wanna come?
The powder's fresh, J-Bae.

1640
01:31:26,596 --> 01:31:28,432
Oh, I got plenty of powder yesterday.

1641
01:31:28,515 --> 01:31:30,517
-Powdered out. So…
-You sure?

1642
01:31:30,600 --> 01:31:32,560
-Uh-huh. Have fun.
-Okay. Give me a kiss.

1643
01:31:32,643 --> 01:31:33,645
-Okay.
-I love you.

1644
01:31:33,728 --> 01:31:35,229
-I love you too. Bye.
-Bye.

1645
01:31:35,312 --> 01:31:36,313
Cute.

1646
01:31:38,023 --> 01:31:39,486
You sure?

1647
01:31:44,737 --> 01:31:49,407
You know, people die at these things?
I saw it on the Internet.

1648
01:31:50,450 --> 01:31:53,954
- It's a gender reveal party.
- They're lethal and stupid.

1649
01:31:54,037 --> 01:31:55,829
Oh, just let 'em make a fuss.

1650
01:31:55,912 --> 01:31:59,249
I mean, I get, you know,
eliminating the surprise

1651
01:31:59,332 --> 01:32:00,751
but it's not party-worthy.

1652
01:32:00,834 --> 01:32:02,710
You know, one
of the great joys of my life

1653
01:32:02,793 --> 01:32:04,379
has been allowing for surprises.

1654
01:32:04,462 --> 01:32:08,340
Remember when you were convinced
that Zach was a girl?

1655
01:32:08,423 --> 01:32:11,134
Well, everything has
to be a party nowadays.

1656
01:32:11,217 --> 01:32:13,386
- You hate parties.
- Everything has to be an event.

1657
01:32:13,469 --> 01:32:15,638
No, no. You hate having fun.

1658
01:32:15,721 --> 01:32:17,807
You know, kids have
preschool graduations now.

1659
01:32:17,890 --> 01:32:19,599
You haven't achieved anything yet.

1660
01:32:20,933 --> 01:32:23,061
Can we just… Can we just enjoy it?

1661
01:32:26,063 --> 01:32:28,315
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Look, lady.

1662
01:32:28,398 --> 01:32:31,129
It's not too healthy to be
coming back here all the time.

1663
01:32:31,859 --> 01:32:33,819
It's important to move on.

1664
01:32:36,030 --> 01:32:37,197
Mmm.

1665
01:32:42,786 --> 01:32:44,036
This is perfect, huh?

1666
01:32:46,205 --> 01:32:47,372
Huh?

1667
01:32:51,751 --> 01:32:52,794
You're okay?

1668
01:32:54,878 --> 01:32:55,879
Yeah.

1669
01:32:56,379 --> 01:32:58,298
-Yeah?
-Just a little cold.

1670
01:33:00,758 --> 01:33:02,718
-Come on.
-Mmm.

1671
01:33:17,773 --> 01:33:20,191
I booked us on a hot air balloon later on.

1672
01:33:22,485 --> 01:33:25,612
And, uh, there's a new couple
in… in unit nine.

1673
01:33:25,695 --> 01:33:27,448
I think they'd, uh… Ooh.

1674
01:33:27,531 --> 01:33:29,450
I think they'd make
great doubles partners.

1675
01:33:29,533 --> 01:33:32,243
If I meet any more new people,
I'm going to explode.

1676
01:33:34,662 --> 01:33:36,563
And then what would you complain about?

1677
01:33:37,330 --> 01:33:38,582
- What?
- Come on, Joanie,

1678
01:33:38,665 --> 01:33:40,125
you love to complain.

1679
01:33:41,126 --> 01:33:43,418
That's not a thing people love.

1680
01:33:46,130 --> 01:33:47,172
You okay?

1681
01:33:48,257 --> 01:33:49,799
I made a mistake.

1682
01:33:51,801 --> 01:33:53,427
Did you lose your skis again?

1683
01:33:56,847 --> 01:33:59,474
No. I, uh…

1684
01:34:03,435 --> 01:34:05,771
I made a mistake coming h-here with you.

1685
01:34:13,443 --> 01:34:14,653
Okay.

1686
01:34:16,113 --> 01:34:17,114
What'd I do wrong now?

1687
01:34:17,197 --> 01:34:22,285
Nothing. Oh, nothing. No, you're perfect.
I know you say you're not b-but you are.

1688
01:34:22,368 --> 01:34:26,246
You're kind and brave and smart.
That's how I know.

1689
01:34:26,329 --> 01:34:29,374
I waited all these years for this.

1690
01:34:30,249 --> 01:34:31,250
This.

1691
01:34:32,251 --> 01:34:35,338
Why can't you just enjoy it?
We're in a literal paradise.

1692
01:34:35,421 --> 01:34:38,840
Yeah, I'm sorry
I didn't realize it sooner.

1693
01:34:38,923 --> 01:34:40,509
I think I just… I think I just

1694
01:34:40,592 --> 01:34:42,593
-got really caught up in everything.
-Joanie, what the…

1695
01:34:42,676 --> 01:34:44,720
And maybe it would've worked
between us in life.

1696
01:34:44,803 --> 01:34:45,805
You know? Maybe not.

1697
01:34:45,888 --> 01:34:48,890
But I-I can't pretend that my world
didn't continue without you.

1698
01:34:48,973 --> 01:34:52,477
I am not asking you to.
I have never asked it of you.

1699
01:34:52,560 --> 01:34:55,020
-Unlike you, I don't hide things.
-Well, what's that supposed to mean?

1700
01:34:55,103 --> 01:34:59,107
I grit my teeth every single day
so you can go to that damn tunnel.

1701
01:35:04,445 --> 01:35:07,280
Joanie, we were happiest together.

1702
01:35:07,363 --> 01:35:09,157
Yeah. Of course we were.

1703
01:35:09,741 --> 01:35:11,535
It was young love. It was…

1704
01:35:11,618 --> 01:35:16,580
It was love without the burden
of a mortgage or a job or kids.

1705
01:35:16,663 --> 01:35:19,666
It was, you know, the kind of love
you feel before knowing loss.

1706
01:35:19,749 --> 01:35:21,375
It was everything, but…

1707
01:35:22,752 --> 01:35:24,336
Love isn't just one happy moment.

1708
01:35:24,419 --> 01:35:26,004
Right? It's a million.

1709
01:35:26,087 --> 01:35:30,842
And it's bickering in the car,
and supporting someone when they need it,

1710
01:35:30,925 --> 01:35:33,970
and it's growing together,
and looking after each other.

1711
01:35:34,053 --> 01:35:36,805
We can grow together now.
We can look after each other now.

1712
01:35:36,888 --> 01:35:39,307
I mean, Luke. Honestly?

1713
01:35:39,390 --> 01:35:41,600
Am I living up to the memory?

1714
01:35:44,102 --> 01:35:48,731
You waited so long in that…
that artificial place,

1715
01:35:48,814 --> 01:35:50,816
but here, this is real.

1716
01:35:51,567 --> 01:35:53,236
And… And you're living and…

1717
01:35:53,944 --> 01:35:57,197
I'm giving you permission.
Go live without me.

1718
01:35:57,280 --> 01:35:59,323
Oh, you're giving me permission? Are you…

1719
01:35:59,406 --> 01:36:00,950
-Are you giving me permission?
-Okay, I'm sorry.

1720
01:36:01,033 --> 01:36:03,286
-That was a little condescending.
-Thank you so much, my Highness.

1721
01:36:03,369 --> 01:36:04,537
-I'm your humble servant.
-Okay.

1722
01:36:04,620 --> 01:36:07,107
-Thank you so much for the permission.
-I'm sorry.

1723
01:36:09,249 --> 01:36:11,000
This is not fair.

1724
01:36:14,628 --> 01:36:15,629
It's not fair.

1725
01:36:17,089 --> 01:36:18,089
I know.

1726
01:36:19,757 --> 01:36:20,758
But…

1727
01:36:22,635 --> 01:36:23,677
I have to go back.

1728
01:36:23,760 --> 01:36:25,262
You out of your mind?

1729
01:36:25,345 --> 01:36:28,223
The moment you step through a red door,
they'll find you.

1730
01:36:29,598 --> 01:36:31,517
They'll put you into the void.

1731
01:36:32,059 --> 01:36:33,143
I have to try.

1732
01:36:34,311 --> 01:36:37,605
No, you don't. You can stay here with me.

1733
01:36:42,317 --> 01:36:43,443
Please stay.

1734
01:36:48,739 --> 01:36:49,824
Please stay.

1735
01:36:56,079 --> 01:36:57,163
I'm sorry.

1736
01:37:00,165 --> 01:37:02,209
I really do love you.

1737
01:37:47,455 --> 01:37:48,622
Okay.

1738
01:37:50,958 --> 01:37:54,419
Hands up, Fenwick. Give me the keys.
You got it, Joanie. You've got it, Joanie.

1739
01:37:54,502 --> 01:37:56,296
Yeah. Stick 'em up, stick 'em up.

1740
01:37:56,379 --> 01:37:57,422
Stick 'em up, Fenny.

1741
01:37:57,505 --> 01:38:00,174
Are you ready to die, Fenny?
You want me to cut you? I'll cut…

1742
01:38:00,257 --> 01:38:01,259
Oh, God.

1743
01:38:01,342 --> 01:38:03,135
Such a sweet boy. He's so sweet.

1744
01:38:03,218 --> 01:38:05,929
Unless I do some… Okay. Yeah.

1745
01:38:06,012 --> 01:38:07,638
You know that won't work.

1746
01:38:09,682 --> 01:38:10,849
I mean…

1747
01:38:12,267 --> 01:38:13,560
It might.

1748
01:38:28,655 --> 01:38:30,574
I can't believe I'm doing this.

1749
01:38:33,619 --> 01:38:35,179
You're gonna need a distraction.

1750
01:38:38,748 --> 01:38:40,332
Luke…

1751
01:38:41,666 --> 01:38:42,918
I'm so sorry.

1752
01:38:43,877 --> 01:38:45,170
Yeah.

1753
01:38:45,962 --> 01:38:47,004
I know.

1754
01:38:53,676 --> 01:38:56,429
So, you remember how
I used to do some local theater?

1755
01:39:12,442 --> 01:39:15,820
Please don't touch the exhibits.
Remember the exhibits aren't real.

1756
01:39:15,903 --> 01:39:17,154
She left.

1757
01:39:19,532 --> 01:39:22,784
- Why?
- Oh, buddy.

1758
01:39:23,535 --> 01:39:26,121
I know. I know it's tough.

1759
01:39:26,204 --> 01:39:27,331
I know, I know.

1760
01:39:27,414 --> 01:39:28,956
But… B-But trust me, it'll get better.

1761
01:39:29,039 --> 01:39:32,918
It's okay. It's okay. Yeah, that's right.
J-Just let it out, big guy.

1762
01:39:33,001 --> 01:39:36,463
Let it out. Let it out. Let it all out.

1763
01:39:36,546 --> 01:39:38,214
Okay? It's okay. It's okay.

1764
01:39:38,297 --> 01:39:40,632
It's tough today,
b-but there's always tomorrow.

1765
01:39:40,715 --> 01:39:42,384
It's tough today,
there's always tomorrow, huh?

1766
01:39:42,467 --> 01:39:44,303
-That's right. That's right. Okay.
-Okay, good.

1767
01:39:44,386 --> 01:39:46,012
I just needed a good cry, I think.

1768
01:39:46,095 --> 01:39:47,347
Yeah, I get that.

1769
01:39:47,430 --> 01:39:49,349
-I remember when my old lady dumped...
-Anyway, thanks.

1770
01:39:49,432 --> 01:39:52,559
I'm gonna pop in for, uh…
For old time's sake.

1771
01:39:53,435 --> 01:39:55,353
Yeah, but y-you didn't take a ticket.

1772
01:39:58,021 --> 01:40:00,232
I need to stop being such a giver.

1773
01:40:13,618 --> 01:40:15,661
You should hurry up.

1774
01:40:17,079 --> 01:40:18,080
Yeah.

1775
01:40:20,749 --> 01:40:21,875
Goodbye, Luke.

1776
01:40:24,085 --> 01:40:25,170
Goodbye, Joan.

1777
01:40:28,380 --> 01:40:29,381
Yeah.

1778
01:41:19,715 --> 01:41:22,092
-Honey, it was the last time, I promise.
-No.

1779
01:41:22,175 --> 01:41:24,636
Will you please just calm down
and let's discuss this?

1780
01:41:24,719 --> 01:41:26,638
- Don't you dare tell me to calm down!
- There she is!

1781
01:41:26,720 --> 01:41:27,721
Stop right there!

1782
01:41:27,804 --> 01:41:29,682
-You are not taking my child!
-What do you care?

1783
01:41:29,765 --> 01:41:32,476
- Get in here right now!
- Stop her! Stop her!

1784
01:41:32,559 --> 01:41:33,560
I hate you!

1785
01:41:33,643 --> 01:41:35,144
…you would treat me like that?

1786
01:41:36,145 --> 01:41:39,606
- What if I'm pregnant?
- It'll be okay, Joanie. I promise.

1787
01:41:40,357 --> 01:41:41,650
I'm sorry, the check bounced.

1788
01:41:41,733 --> 01:41:43,026
Please.

1789
01:41:43,109 --> 01:41:44,569
- I love you.
- I love you.

1790
01:41:46,153 --> 01:41:48,197
There's nowhere to go!

1791
01:41:48,280 --> 01:41:51,938
- We're sorry for your loss.
- No, no, no, no.

1792
01:41:54,369 --> 01:41:56,612
Come on, come on, come on! Hurry up!

1793
01:42:00,040 --> 01:42:01,041
Stop!

1794
01:42:09,756 --> 01:42:10,757
Shit.

1795
01:42:18,097 --> 01:42:19,265
Jesus, Larry. I don't wanna...

1796
01:42:19,348 --> 01:42:21,099
I don't wanna have
this conversation again. I am...

1797
01:42:21,182 --> 01:42:23,393
No, I am not.
I am not comparing you to him!

1798
01:42:23,476 --> 01:42:26,812
No, I have never compared you to him!
And I don't wanna have this conversation!

1799
01:42:26,895 --> 01:42:28,147
It's humiliating, Joan.

1800
01:42:28,230 --> 01:42:29,523
-I can't do this anymore.
-Don't move!

1801
01:42:29,606 --> 01:42:32,400
God, well, she brought it up.
What am I supposed to say?

1802
01:42:32,483 --> 01:42:34,110
I mean, I… I get it. She doesn't like me.

1803
01:42:34,193 --> 01:42:35,987
-No, no, she literally said…
-You'll grow on her.

1804
01:42:36,070 --> 01:42:37,780
- … "I don't like him."
- You grow on people, Larry.

1805
01:42:37,863 --> 01:42:39,990
Great.
I'm like a fungus. I'm a mushroom.

1806
01:43:08,013 --> 01:43:09,515
Upstairs! Upstairs!

1807
01:43:09,598 --> 01:43:10,765
Larry.

1808
01:43:13,435 --> 01:43:14,435
Hurry!

1809
01:43:15,311 --> 01:43:17,980
Come on, get up. Grab her! Grab her!

1810
01:43:28,697 --> 01:43:30,532
Okay.

1811
01:43:52,884 --> 01:43:55,886
Train delay on Platform 186.

1812
01:43:55,969 --> 01:43:57,763
Escapee on the tracks.

1813
01:44:05,936 --> 01:44:07,355
Excuse me. Hi.

1814
01:44:07,437 --> 01:44:11,399
I-I need to know which eternity
Larry Cutler went to.

1815
01:44:11,900 --> 01:44:14,986
Ma'am, there have been
425,000 Larry Cutlers.

1816
01:44:15,069 --> 01:44:16,445
Could you be more specific?

1817
01:44:20,740 --> 01:44:21,741
Oh.

1818
01:44:23,826 --> 01:44:26,370
Shoot, oh, shoot, oh, shoot.

1819
01:44:26,453 --> 01:44:29,748
Red door escapee.
Do not engage.

1820
01:44:30,666 --> 01:44:31,666
Excuse me.

1821
01:44:34,960 --> 01:44:37,754
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.

1822
01:44:39,506 --> 01:44:42,843
You know,
I've been thinking a lot about it and,

1823
01:44:42,926 --> 01:44:47,179
you know, I-I think that maybe
we should consider being poly.

1824
01:44:47,262 --> 01:44:49,931
I'm not much
of a multitasker, babe.

1825
01:44:50,014 --> 01:44:51,474
-What?
-I'm a one-woman man.

1826
01:44:51,557 --> 01:44:52,559
Oh, real...

1827
01:44:52,642 --> 01:44:54,886
-Oh, my God.
-Watch where you're going, lady.

1828
01:44:55,435 --> 01:44:57,094
Go over there. Over there.

1829
01:44:58,897 --> 01:45:00,524
You guys see a woman
come running this way?

1830
01:45:00,607 --> 01:45:02,692
-No.
-She went that way.

1831
01:45:02,775 --> 01:45:04,485
-Thanks. Come on. Let's go.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1832
01:45:04,568 --> 01:45:05,695
Good luck, you guys.

1833
01:45:06,737 --> 01:45:07,862
Let's go. Move.

1834
01:45:08,571 --> 01:45:09,990
Joan.

1835
01:45:10,073 --> 01:45:11,867
You're such a romantic.

1836
01:45:11,950 --> 01:45:14,493
We can sneak her into one
of those old, disused eternities.

1837
01:45:14,576 --> 01:45:16,287
Not one of the racist ones.
But you'll be safe there.

1838
01:45:16,370 --> 01:45:18,706
-Security never checks them.
-Where did he go?

1839
01:45:18,789 --> 01:45:19,789
Who?

1840
01:45:19,872 --> 01:45:21,166
Where's Larry?

1841
01:45:21,249 --> 01:45:24,044
Oh, my God. I knew it.
I knew it. I knew it.

1842
01:45:24,127 --> 01:45:26,712
Where is he?

1843
01:45:57,529 --> 01:45:58,530
Oh.

1844
01:46:00,282 --> 01:46:01,907
It's a lot out there, huh?

1845
01:46:03,617 --> 01:46:04,744
Intense.

1846
01:46:05,494 --> 01:46:06,494
Yeah.

1847
01:46:06,995 --> 01:46:10,290
I know somewhere you could really unwind.

1848
01:46:10,373 --> 01:46:12,458
Come on, Marge. You know the rules.

1849
01:46:12,541 --> 01:46:14,460
I'm just trying to help a girl out.

1850
01:46:14,960 --> 01:46:16,503
I know what I want now.

1851
01:46:18,379 --> 01:46:20,131
I could show you my eternity.

1852
01:46:20,214 --> 01:46:22,258
It's, uh, just around the corner.

1853
01:46:25,343 --> 01:46:26,636
You heard the lady.

1854
01:46:29,347 --> 01:46:31,098
I preferred the last barman.

1855
01:46:38,688 --> 01:46:40,649
You look like you could use a drink.

1856
01:46:40,732 --> 01:46:41,733
Oh.

1857
01:46:44,026 --> 01:46:45,027
Yeah.

1858
01:46:45,694 --> 01:46:47,196
You never left.

1859
01:46:48,071 --> 01:46:49,072
Nah.

1860
01:46:49,155 --> 01:46:51,574
Sand really does get everywhere.

1861
01:46:52,408 --> 01:46:56,912
Yeah. Turns out
that the cold is just cold.

1862
01:47:12,049 --> 01:47:14,343
-Is that for you?
-Oh, yeah.

1863
01:47:14,426 --> 01:47:16,053
I'm kind of a fugitive.

1864
01:47:16,678 --> 01:47:17,846
Where you gonna go?

1865
01:47:19,847 --> 01:47:21,098
I know a place.

1866
01:47:22,975 --> 01:47:24,226
It could be dangerous.

1867
01:47:34,568 --> 01:47:36,069
When do we leave?

1868
01:48:03,676 --> 01:48:06,302
Well, looks like Oakdale.

1869
01:48:08,471 --> 01:48:09,472
It's perfect.

